        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You have always had a thing for the highway.  It did dnot matter where you were aslong as you had gas int he tank and the road in front of you.  You started driving for a law firm when you were in high school, running documents over summer vacations.  After graduation your former eployerd offered you a college loan.  You stuck out two years of pre law before deciding that forty years of office work would kill you faster than hitting an overpass support pylon.  The next semesters tuition paid for a security driving course and shooting lessons and two months later you were a certified bonded courier.  A years workd paid off the loan, another two paid off your car then you were your own person.  \n\nYou stayed with legitimate work despite some tempting offers to play drug mule, it was too risky, even if you did not go to jail you would lose all your licenses.  But you saw a pattern in the the jobs you were getting.  Regular run from Baltimore to New York for medical stuff, New York to Boston and back with refrigerated cases.  Alway moving between nameless industrial parks with a tight deadline.  You asked some discreet questions, more to make sure you were not carrying anything illegal than out of personal curiousity.\n\nOne of yoru inquireis was not discreet enough.  Your employers decided that you were too valuable to their operation to kill so they let you in on the secret."
        ],
